<subSubSection pageId="155" pageNumber="156" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Scaphinotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scaphinotus</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826: 17. Type species: 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elevatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Carabus elevatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1787 by monotypy. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">scaphos</emphasis>
(barque, nacelle, skiff) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">notos</emphasis>
(back, upper surface), presumably alluding to the shape of the pronotum of the sole species known to Dejean which has the sides of the pronotum markedly turned out (&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
bords 
<normalizedToken originalValue="latéraux">lateraux</normalizedToken>
du corselet 
<normalizedToken originalValue="très-déprimés">tres-deprimes</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="relevés">releves</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot;) giving the impression of a small boat [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Agassiz" authorityYear="1846" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Scaphonotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scaphonotus</taxonomicName>
Agassiz, 1846: 332. Unjustified emendation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Scaphinotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Scaphinotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
